race.comment: EMPRESS OF JAPAN (3) capable mare who gets out to her right distance range second-up. Produced a good set of figures first-up when closing late to run fifth over 1100m at this track. Maps well and sure to be thereabouts. THE MONA LISA (6) nice mare who keeps raising the bar. Rounded them up effortlessly on resumption to salute over 1300m at Goulburn in a decent contest. Comes to the provincials for the first time and she looks up to the task. FAST TRACK (7) resuming. Sprinted well to salute as fav on debut before her form dropped off at her next three outings. Fitted with the two searching trials and gets her chance from the inside gate. ZOE (5) kept fresh when up in grade for a fading eighth over 1300m at Randwick Kensington in BM72 class. Gets weight relief with the claim and can add value to the exotics.
